"Steven" == Steven A Swiniarski <gb485@cleveland.Freenet.Edu> writes:

Steven> I herby transfer a kudo from General Chaos to Oerjan, because
Steven> repealing the FM Rule just because it has a temporary effect
Steven> on Voting patterns is roughly akin to repealing the Virus
Steven> because it made our lives difficult by infecting the TO Rule.

If that was the only problem I would not have resigned the
Assessorship in protest.  The problem is that the FM both creates a
considerable degree of uncertainty on its own (by constantly
disrupting the Rules) and, worse, compounds the uncertainity that is
everpresent from routine play.  It's not just one particular Rule
Change that was problematic; it's an endemic problem that I have with
_all_ random and automatic Rule Changes.  (I also intend to support
the Proposal to repeal the Virus--assuming it is even possible to vote
on that Proposal; I can't tell.  If there had not been such a Proposal
extant, I would have made one myself.)

Furthermore, neither the Virus nor the Frankenstein Mutator slow down
for a Crisis.  They just keep right on firing away at the Ruleset,
making it ever harder to right the Game when it founders.  And as
Assessor I have been taking a great deal of the incoming fire, simply
by virtue of holding the Game's most complex Office.  This Game _does
not function_ without the Assessor.  Making the Office of Assessor
impossible or overly burdensome for any Player to perform is suicidal.

I expected to lose a Kudo over this affair, but over my precipitous
resignation of the Assessorship, not over my proper targeting of the
FM as a severe source of instability and dysfunction in Agora's
Rules.  

Oh, by the way: I hereby transfer one Kudo from Swann for not
appreciating the importance of Officers, and especially the Assessor,
to Michael, as compensation for dumping the Assessorship into his lap
unexpectedly.

